1
00:00:00,210 --> 00:00:06,500
I appreciate that song. I'd never heard that one. Wasn't that great? It's an amazing thing how God

2
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:13,500
can take ancient words and make them current for us, make them very present and life-changing for

3
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:19,300
us. It's one of the privileges over the years as a pastor that I've gotten to see that in people's

4
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:26,540
lives, and it never ceases to amaze me. It's good to be in our own church back at Fullerton. I know

5
00:00:26,540 --> 00:00:31,920
for some of you who I don't know quite as well, it might seem odd that here's this member of the

6
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,140
church who hardly ever is here, but I am in other places. Let me share with you a little bit about

7
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:42,980
the last couple of weeks where we've been, because it sort of tells a story of what my ministry is

8
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:49,640
about in this phase of my life. Two weeks ago, we were up in Templeton, California. It's the

9
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:54,840
northernmost church in the American Baptist Church's Pacific Southwest, a church that has

10
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:59,880
always been small but two years ago was on the verge of closing they were down to about a dozen

11
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:06,380
people and a new pastor came and the church has been growing again now they were about a dozen

12
00:01:06,380 --> 00:01:11,720
two years ago now they're at about 40 so that's not dramatic but percentage wise that's pretty

13
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:16,320
good growth one of the interesting thing that's things that's happened there is that beginning

14
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:22,020
about a year ago they began to see a number of people make first-time professions of faith in

15
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:27,640
Christ and this last year they baptized quite a number of people if I'm remembering correctly it

16
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:32,920
was nine which in a church of less than 40 on most of their Sundays nine is a pretty good

17
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:37,820
percentage they might just get the per capita baptism award in the region next year I was

18
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:43,080
telling the pastor and God is definitely doing some things within that church and it was such

19
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:50,400
a blessing to see last Sunday Elaine and I were in Las Vegas and in one of our new church plants

20
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:58,350
Progressive Pilgrim Church. Progressive Pilgrim came out of a church split with Unity Baptist

21
00:01:58,350 --> 00:02:07,280
Church. Strange that Unity split, but God did something special out of that. The split was messy

22
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:16,500
and some of the region's staff went in to help and God was really wonderful in the way he worked

23
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:23,840
in both those two congregations after the split, because at the annual conference last October,

24
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,940
the pastor began to share with me some of what the Lord had done in healing between the

25
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:34,020
